$ PowerShell module outlook: invoke-scriptBlockOnOutlookMails
@ invoke-scriptBlockOnOutlookMails

`invoke-scriptBlockOnOutlookMails` (of the Powershell Module → Windows/PowerShell/modules/personal/Outlook[Outlook]) iterates over each mail in the inbox and the sent folder and
calls the script block that was provided as argument to the function.

An example of a function that uses `invoke-scriptBlockOnOutlookMails` is `→ Windows/PowerShell/modules/personal/Outlook/send-outlookMail`.
